text:
Tianmu Mountain is a mountain near Hangzhou in Zhejiang Province, China. It has two high points ("peaks"). The taller peak, or, is 1506 meters high. is 1480 meters high.
Its Chinese name "Tiānmùshān" () means "Mountain of the Heavenly Eyes" because there is a lake on top of each of the two peaks.
There are several rare species of plants and animals on Tianmu Mountain. The only five trees in the world are on Tianmu Mountain.
